{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"956d5881-7950-4ce9-9cb6-3785867a5e28","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` **natively supports Microsoft Testing Platform**, so you **no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`**. That property was a bridge for .NET 9 SDK; in .NET 10, MTP integration is built-in.\n\nSince you already have `EnableMSTestRunner` set, you just need to remove the now-unnecessary property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_Kg3dVE38Q2NQVQDZ6oiRKr","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_V74P2Z9S2kRI9tiu1Geib9","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-2c0224922d6c4abdbc2b156e338524cc/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-2c0224922d6c4abdbc2b156e338524cc/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"6263868b-c834-422c-b9e8-59f437100a9f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me provide accurate information.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Starting with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` uses MTP by default when the test project is an MTP-based project (i.e., it has `EnableMSTestRunner` or similar runner enabled).\n\nSo they can remove `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` since .NET 10 SDK's `dotnet test` natively integrates with MTP.\n\n\nLet me verify this is correct and help them update their project configuration accordingly.","outputTokens":513,"requestId":"E3DD:229C6C:15E11A9:188793E:6A0520E9"},"id":"87407a89-1754-4846-b5b7-2a85948c67e2","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:10:10.939Z