{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6ac97f51-fcce-4048-93e1-94d68273231f","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n| Property | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `EnableMSTestRunner` | **Keep** — tells MSTest to produce an executable test host |\n| `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` | **Removed** — .NET 10 `dotnet test` natively speaks MTP |\n\n**What changed in .NET 10:** `dotnet test` directly communicates with MTP-based test hosts via its native protocol. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was a .NET 9-era opt-in to bridge the old VSTest adapter path — it's unnecessary (and ignored) on .NET 10.\n\nYour `dotnet test` will now use MTP out of the box. No other changes needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6263868b-c834-422c-b9e8-59f437100a9f","outputTokens":179,"requestId":"E3DD:229C6C:15E3C9E:188AA9D:6A0520F5"},"id":"0c048733-a0cd-4a46-9e82-7ca268c835cb","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:10:20.327Z","parentId":"e1bce792-cf7d-4fc7-bfe9-263d0f56e453"}
